parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vibration or shaking of the steering wheel can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-miss situations, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The steering wheel shakes or vibrates while driving
and front end; the vibration can be seen visually when hands are removed from the steering wheel; the vehicle may feel unstable or unsafe at highway speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Water Ingestion into Air Filter Housing
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water ingestion into the air filter housing can cause the engine to hydrolock, leading to costly repairs, engine damage, and potentially even accidents due to loss of power and stalling.
symptoms: Water damage and rot on the air filter
glow plug light on the dash

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a burning odor and smoke inside the cabin, potentially leading to a fire hazard, and can also cause the vehicle to turn off spontaneously while in motion, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: smoke coming from the front console or under the hood
vehicle turns off spontaneously while in motion
no warning or predictability of the shutdown.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the seat heater can cause burns to occupants and damage to the seat and surrounding components.
The failure of the starter system can cause the vehicle to fail to start, and can also lead to electrical system failures, potentially causing a fire hazard.
symptoms: Starter button clicks but does not start the vehicle
smoke coming from under the hood.
